    <h1>The History of Hot Wheels</h1>
    <p>Hot Wheels was introduced by American toy maker Mattel in 1968 as a new line of die-cast toy cars. Instantly popular among children and collectors alike, Hot Wheels revolutionized the toy car industry by combining quality craftsmanship with exciting designs and performance features.</p>
    <p>Since its launch, Hot Wheels has produced thousands of car models, including real-life vehicles and fantastical designs. The brand expanded into tracks, playsets, and video games, building a passionate community of enthusiasts worldwide.</p>
    <p>Hot Wheels remains one of the most iconic toy brands in the world, celebrated for creativity, nostalgia, and innovation.</p>

